vista handwriting recognition with a pen tablet language center technology resources language center technology resources vista handwriting recognition with a pen tablet from language center technology resources jump to navigation search title vista handwriting recognition with a pen tablet i have a dell precision m4300 running vista ultimate and i installed my wacom graphire bluetooth tablet i had to download the driver for vista from the wacom website but once i did it ran quite well in fact there is a small tab on the left side of the screen that i can click to get a handwriting input box on that box there is a language setting much like the normal language bar in windows and i can select another languge just by clicking on a button i selected japanese and lo and behold it was able to recognize poorly written characters from the pen and insert them into applications like msword this has always been possible in english in xp but this was the first time i have seen the seemless integration of the language setting with handwriting recognition retrieved from http www stanford edu group lc admin cgi bin lcatswiki index php vista_handwriting_recognition_with_a_pen_ _tablet views page discussion view source history personal tools log in login with webauth search this wiki navigation main page coursework audio and video orientations and communications online tools what about toolbox what links here related changes special pages printable version permanent link powered by mediawiki this page was last modified on 10 august 2011 at 11 24 this page has been accessed 40 times privacy policy about language center technology resources disclaimers
